{
  "doc_id": "43672",
  "text": "Very surprisingly, recruitment of new CENP-A to centromeric chromatin is not contemporaneous with replication of centromere DNA. Rather, it is restricted to a brief interval in G1 immediately following mitosis in human cells [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and slightly earlier in anaphase in the rapidly dividing Drosophila syncytial embryo [CITATION_3] . The assembly of new CENP-A nucleosomes in early G1 is coincident with the accumulation of the Mis18 complex (Mis18a, Mis18b, and Mis18BP1/hsKNL2) at the centromere [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . CENP-A loading is dependent on this complex for assembly, although no direct interaction has been observed between CENP-A and Mis18.",
